TutorialText: Your mission is to match 3 tiles that are the same.  You may move one at a time either up and down or side to side.  You can only move a tile one space.  If the tile does not create a match when moved_ it will revert back to its original position.

Story: The day that Drumstick and Waffleton had begun construction on their diner, Waffleton had found an old hammer lying in the dirt.

Supposing it to be some discarded thing, he began to swing his arm to throw the hammer away.  But in that moment... that moment where the hammer swung... Waffleton felt a sensation flow through his arm.

It was like electricty had awoken inside of him! He could sense the thoughts of the hammer and it could sense its belonging to him!  The hammer possessed a magical ability to smash even the most unsmashable of things.

Upon swinging his hammer that first time, its power was so spectacular that merely swinging it deserved its own name.  And so, in that first swing was the birth of the the most extradorinary of things.  Thus was born........The Waffle Smash.
TutorialText: Congratulations!  You have been awarded the Waffle Smash!  When you select the Waffle Smash from the square to the right of the gameboard_ you can then tap on any tile and Waffleton will walk onto the board and whack that tile into oblivion!

Congratulations!  You have just been awarded your first recipe!  Your diner is now able to start selling Belgian Waffles. Your recipe card has been added to your inventory.  You may access your inventory now through the main menu to view your recipes.

Story: Waffleton and Drumstick had gotten their diner up and running and boy was it turning into a smash success!  Customers were just coming from everywhere!  Business was booming!

Until….until…. Until Grumpy Frank.  Grumpy Frank came in one day and sat down with his grumpy mouth and his grumpy face.  Grumpy Frank didn't want waffles.  Grumpy Frank wanted only one thing.  Coffee.  Just coffee.  A look of dismay came over the Chicken & Waffle duo as they realized that they could no longer have a waffle diner with no coffee.  It was a travesty indeed!

The only solution was that they had to go and find a vendor who could hook them up with that sweet and tasty java. It was time for the caffeine.  It was time to turn Grumpy Franks frown upside down!  Now if they could only just find that coffee...

One day while pondering their Grumpy Frank dilemma, one of Waffleton's vendors showed up to the diner with some sweet beans from Columbia!  He'd brought that jungle java, that high octane boost juice, the caffeine crave to make you be-have! It was that Premium Columbian coffee!

The moment Waffleton announced the addition of Coffee to their diner menu, the crowds went wild!  There were parades in his name! Centaurs roamed the streets!  Um..ok.. not really.  But some of the customers really liked it!

Except for one.  Yup...you guessed it.  Grumpy Frank.  Grumpy Frank just kept raving about how Peruvian Coffee was so much better than Columbian Coffee and that he could never be satisfied with second best.
Determined to see a smile on everyone's face, including Grumpy Frank, Waffleton set out to find those Peruvian Coffee Beans!  It was time to go on a mission.  It was time to go... to Peru!

TutorialText: To use the coffee booster_ if you run out of moves on a particular level_ don’t worry.  You just got tired.  Its nothing that some coffee can't fix!  Use a coffee to gain the energy for 5 extra moves!  This will automatically pop up as an option if you run out of moves as long as you picked coffee as one of your boosters.

Story: It was a sunny afternoon when Waffleton arrived in Peru.  While there, he discovered that the Alpaca was a noble creature.  He also discovered that standing next to an alpaca was a risky endeavor for a waffle.

After the alpaca incident, Waffleton was feeling a bit lighter and met an ancient peruvian coffee monk.  Unfortunately, the monk had taken a vow of silence and could offer no help.  On his shoulder, however, was a small fly who was casually munching on an apple.  The fly was looking around, serene and zen.  He had mastered the ways of the monks and was at one with the apple he was eating.

While the fly was indeed a master coffee farmer, a trait learned from the monks, what he really wanted was to come and live in the United States.  He had heard about a big apple in the United States and was determined to see this big apple for himself!

It had always been his fly dream, for he was no ordinary fly.  He was a fruit fly!  But he could not get to America by himself. Once there, he would need a job to save enough money to see this big apple and so, he made a deal with Waffleton.

If Waffleton agreed to let Fly come and work for him in the Diner, then Fly would give Waffleton the monk's prized creation...Peruvian Dream Coffee Beans!  They had a taste so sweet that there's no need to speak! And so a deal was struck!  What Waffleton did not know at the time was how useful little Fly could be.  Fly wasn't just a genius with the java.  When it came time to make matches, Fly had a whole new bag of tricks up his sleeve!

TutorialText: You have acquired the fly!  Fly will appear on your gameboard.  You can also make more of him by matching 4 tiles in the shape of a square.  When you use fly to make a match of 3 or more_ he will fly off of the board and then divebomb key tiles to help you!  If you drag a fly to another fly tile_ get ready to watch a fly tornado start wreaking havoc on the tiles!  It looks like there is a match available for you to match fly to two tiles of the same color.  Why don't you start the level and give that a try?

Story: Waffleton finally returned back to the diner from Peru!  Wouldn't you know it, but there was Grumpy Frank sitting on the same diner stool that he always sat on, that same grumpy look on his face.

Waffleton stood in front of Grumpy Frank as he slowly pulled the bag of Peruvian Dream coffee beans out of his knap sack.  As the bag came into view, something happened that had never happened before.  In all the history of all of the world and since the beginning of time...ok...well...since the day the diner opened...NO ONE had ever seen Grumpy Frank be anything other than, well, grumpy.

It began as a twitch in the corner of his mouth.  Was it a nervous tic?  Was it a facial twitch?  Was it a sneeze that lost control?  The twitch broke into surprise...which then turned into...gulp...yup.  A smile.  Grumpy Frank had become....just Frank.

Frank smiled as Waffleton poured him a cup of the Peruvian Dream and then Frank pulled something out of his coat pocket.  It was a gift.  Frank was so happy that he decided to give Waffleton something to help him in his endeavors.

You see, Frank worked construction and had access to things that go ""boom"", things that could help Waffleton make it through the game!  And so Frank handed Waffleton the next tool he would need in finding supplies for his diner.  The Waffle Boom."

TutorialText: Congratulations!  You have unlocked the Waffle Boom!  To use the Waffle Boom_ select it from your Boosters.  Once selected_ tap on any square on the gameboard and watch Waffleton huck that boom!

Story: Waffleton and Drumstick just couldn't get enough of the Waffle Boom.  They were blowing up tiles here and blowing up tiles there!  But for all of their explosive fun, there was one thing they just couldn't seem to find.

Waffleton and Drumstick just couldn't get enough of the Waffle Boom.  They were blowing up tiles here and blowing up tiles there!  But for all of their explosive fun, there was one thing they just couldn't seem to find.

You see, they had collected several recipes now and the diner was up and running, but each recipe was able to upgraded and yet they couldn't seem to find the food ingredients needed to begin upgrading those recipes.   Whatever were they to do?!?

Whatever were they to do?!?, Suddenly, a bright light filled the sky!  A supernova had illuminated the galaxy and as it burned bright, something began to fall from the sky.  Ingredients!  All kinds of ingredients!
Pickles!  Onions!  Mushrooms!  My goodness, it was raining food!  There was only one thing to do now... it was time to go find those ingredients!

Every time you make a match that leads to another and then another or more, you will find food ingredients, but, you gotta beat the level to keep them!  So go my little Waffle Smasher, GO!  Go and start smashin!
The diner business was finally in full swing!  Waffleton and Drumstick were finding food ingredients and working on upgrading their recipes, but the diner was still missing something.
The diner business was finally in full swing!  Waffleton and Drumstick were finding food ingredients and working on upgrading their recipes, but the diner was still missing something.
It needed some entertainment!  And what better entertainment was there than a palace where Waffle's could raffle?  And so Waffleton created the Diner's most precious gem...The Waffle Raffle Palace!

Waffleton and Drumstick were finally there!  Real diner owners!  Sure there were problems just like with any diner, but they were HAPPY!  Well, happy until…until HE walked in.  There he was in his nicely pressed cheap suit.  He smelled of polyester and cheap strawberries.  His eyes were cold and lifeless.  Even the fly couldn't imagine landing on him.  He was an agent of.....*gulp*  the Waffle Revenue Service.   His only mission was AUDIT AUDIT AUDIT.  He cared nothing for Waffleton or Drumstick's happiness.  If he could snatch it away from them, he considered it a bonus.  And if he could put their diner out of business, that would be like a vacation to him.  He didn't care that he worked for the people.  He despised the people.  And he had found a discrepancy! Waffleton had meant to donate money to the Distraught Pancake Charity to get a tax write off.  Instead, he had found himself purchasing the new bass boat 2000 with the super duper quiet motor.  Fun?  Yessiree!!!  Tax write off?  Um...not so much. So now, Waffleton needed to find a way to come up with some moo-lah fast.  How could he make money out of thin air?  And then it came to him... the Waffle Bucks challenge.  But only the best of the best dared even attempt it!  Well, its a good thing that you just found 2 challenge coins and $250WB!

Waffleton and Drumstick had been working long hours in that hot kitchen, bringing people their food and making people smile.   The only problem was that nobody was tipping them!  And in a restaurant of all places!  Well, that just wasn't going to do.  Waffleton began rummaging through the closet where they kept the mop and broom and then he saw it!  It was there and shiny in all of its glory.  It was a jar, made for tips!  It was a tip jar!!!!  To use it though, it seemed that he was going to have to get to it first.  It was stuck behind very heavy things!  It was going to be a challenge.  It was going to be a tip jar challenge!  Can you rise to the challenge?

Waffleton and Drumstick had found that the best part of their day was collecting ingredients to make new and exciting recipes!  The only problem was that sometimes they would get an ingredient they REEEAAAAAALLY needed, only to then lose the level they were playing and not get to keep it!  Awwwww.  How sad for them!  It was just enough to break your itty bitty heart.  They needed to find a way to save those ingredients from getting thrown out when a level was lost...and in a kitchen like theirs, there had to be something.  And then a funny thing happened.  A salesman walked in from the street.  He walked right up to Waffleton and showed him a beautiful sight.  It was a bright shiny new colander!  Shoot, I'll bet the loss of a level would just flow right through that thing and leave all those yummi ingredients safe inside for your inventory.  Why don't you try selecting the colander as one of your boosters on the next level and see if it doesn't become the most useful tool you ever did see!

TutorialText: Congratulations!  You have found and unlocked the Colander!  Be sure to select the colander as one of your boosters on this level!   This means you will not have one of the other 3 as you can only have a maximum of 3 boosters.  This little guy is super helpful though!  If you lose a level_ the colander will automatically pop up and ask you if you want to use it to save the ingredients from that level.  If you don't need the ingredients_ then let them go_ but_ if you do_ you'll be glad you had the colander!

Story: "Waffleton and Drumstick were talking one day while they were cooking up a storm in the kitchen.  Drumstick was polishing an old oil lamp that he thought would make a nice counter decoration.  He didn't know where he'd gotten it, but it would look SOOOOOO nice if he could just get it clean!  So he polished harder and harder and harder...and then SUDDENLY...WITHOUT WARNING...the ground began to SHAAAAAAKE!  Smoke began to pour out of the oil lamp, filling the diner with it's purple glow.  When the smoke began to clear, there stood in front of them a pers....no...not a person.  Some......thing.  Some..... being.  The being bellowed ""I am the genie of the lamp and you are hereby granted ONE and ONLY ONE wish!""  The duo were flabbergasted.  Just as Drumstick was about to ask for World Peace, Waffleton blurted out ""I don't like that i can only make matches with tiles that are next to each other.  Can you make it so that i can move a tile from anywhere on the board to anywhere on the board?""  ""THAT ....THAT.... is what you asked for?"" Exclaimed Drumstick.  It was too late for World Peace.  The most they could hope for was to put on some MJ while they went out searching for more ingredients, and so they did.  They decided to test the capabilities of their newfound ability...they called it The Waffle Switch!"

TutorialText: Congratulations!  You have unlocked the Waffle Switch!  To use Waffle Switch_ after selecting it_ tap on any tile anywhere.  Once it is highlighted_ then tap on any other tile anywhere else and the two will  instantly switch.  They do not have to make a match.  Be sure to select Waffle Switch as one of your 3 boosters first though.  Why don't you give it a try?

Story: Well, our heroes had been working hard.  After having beaten 230 levels, they were plum tuckered out.  Wouldn't you be?  Well, they had finally earned a well deserved vacation to get away from everything for a little while.  The best part of a vacation is that when they would leave for a week and then come back, the diner would have been running for that entire week, just generating more of those oh so needed Waffle Bucks!  To us humans, such a vacation happened in the blink of an eye.  What do you say?  You want to send our unlikely heroes on a vacation and see how much money the diner makes in the week that they are gone? (Remember...for us, it will only be like a few seconds has passed!)

"Waffleton was feeling bad.  He had promised the fly that he would give him work when he came to America, but so far, Waffleton just hadn't had any. Until now.  Waffleton began to realize that the delivery service Waffle Dash was delivering food from restaurants all over town but him and Drumstick were still only serving people the old way.  They needed dashers to work for them!  However could they manage such a thing?  There were only two of them!  And that is where fly came in.  Fly was a natural born leader, a conneisseur of apples, and the right bug for the job!  To commemorate this momentous occasion, Waffleton wrote a song.  ""Fly Fly, he's our man, if he can't do it, no one can!"".  It was an original piece.  He made it all up himself.  Just ask him.  Honest truth.  No lie.  Wouldn't fib.  Nope nope.  No plageurism there.  He came up with it by jus' biden his time.  Songwriting skills aside, Fly was completely enamoured with his duties and was ready to report to work.  The only issue is that fly needed bananas to eat as payment and, well, the diner was just plum out.  They would have to find a way to pick their own apples.  It was going to be a challenge...."

Fly has just become the best little worker.  All of the customers love him.  (The Players too.  Don't lie.  You know you do!).  Quickly having become a fan favorite, Waffleton began to recognize the wisdom of fly.  Fly had achieved oneness with the world of fruit and Waffleton had a problem that only one who was one with the universe could possibly handle.  You see, there were obstacles showing up on the gameboard that Waffle Booms just weren't doing much against.  Those pancake stacks were making things difficult for Waffleton.  He knew that there had to be a way to get rid of those stacks all at once, but he just couldn't seem to figure it out.  And so, he brought his dilemma to fly.  Fly's wisdom astounded him.  It floored him.  It flattened him...ok...actually he just slipped on syrup and fell on the floor, BUUUUUT, fly still had a solution.  Deep in the Peruvian jungle where fly had come from was an ancient herb called Ayhuywannaeatah.  If Waffleton were to eat Ayhuwannaeata, he would suddenly develop a stomach that could eat large quantities of pancakes in a single bite.  It was so crazy that it just....might.....work...if only they had some.   Fly had just not been able to leave his peruvian paradise without taking a bit of home with him. Out of his bag, he produced a single vial of Ayhuywannaeata. With a gulp and a sigh, Waffleton plopped the herb in his mouth and then chewed it up and swallowed it.  Suddenly....he felt a tingling.  It began rumbling deep from within his stomach.  It was like a monster was awakening from the deepest part of his waffly crispness and suddenly... He was ready to munch! It was like a superpower!  He named his newfound ability the Waffle Munch!

"Syrup was here and syrup was there.  Truth be told, syrup was everywhere!   And it was muddling up Waffleton's ability to tear through his beloved match 3 gameboard in pursuit of his precious ingredients.  There had to be a way to even the playing field.  Perhaps a way to stop the syrup from spreading maybe?  Drumstick began laughing at the dilemma, the solution seeming too obvious to him while completely eluding Waffleton.  ""Maybe you should, um, suck it up?""  Drumstick said.  ""With What?""  Asked Waffleton.  Drumstick reached into the sink and pulled it out slowly.  And in his hand was such a simple answer.  Waffleton couldn't believe it was that simple.  And he was right, it wasn't.  But maybe if he could connect 20 of them together to make a big one?  And so waffleton got his craft kit out and began going to work!  After many moons and much hard work, he had finally developed the prototype of... The Waffle Sponge.  It was time to suck!"

The diner was doing well finally, but building had gotten slow.  What once took days now took weeks to add on a new addition to the diner.  Waffleton and Drumstick began looking for a way to make more money.  What they really needed was to attract more customers and, to do that, they needed to add more items to their menu.  The problem was they didn't have enough cooks to do so.  Unless....unless just maybe.... What if Fly could cook?!?!?!  So they asked Fly if he could cook.  Without missing a beat, Fly laid down a sick beat.  As a seasoned beat boxer, he could make sounds that no one had ever heard before.  Truthfully, he made a few that no one WANTED to hear.  But as a cook, he was uncontested.  He could make a butter sauce that would rival a King's.  He could make a smoothie that turned a storm cloud into a rainbow.  He fired up the grill and whipped up the best grilled cheese sammies that had ever been made on this side of the Rio Grande.  As Drumstick and Waffleton stuffed themselves, they looked at each other and nodded.  They had found their extra cook.  There was just one dilemma...Fly only worked for one thing and it wasn't money.  Yup... he needed more apples!  And in order to get apples, well, that means that it's time for another challenge...
